# NSynth AFTER Timbre Embedding Visualization — quality combinations

This notebook loads the pre-extracted `AFTER_Timbre` embeddings from NSynth and visualizes them using:

- PCA
- t-SNE
- UMAP
- K-Means clustering

Compared with the previous version, the multi-label `qualities` vector is not reduced to the first active quality. Instead, each example is assigned to its full active quality combination. For readability, the ten most frequent combinations in the visualization subset are kept as individual categories and all remaining combinations are grouped as `other`.

The notebook also computes two K-Means clusterings:

- one with `k` equal to the number of instrument families present in the loaded subset
- one with `k = 10`, matching the ten most frequent quality combinations

